On the Settings (gear) -> Links page of a repository:

It would be very helpful to allow a list (comma or pipe separated, perhaps) of JIRA project keys when creating/editing a Link to JIRA.

Currently, you either have to create a whole series of JIRA Links (all with the same URL), or use a Custom Link with a crazy regex like this:

{code}
#!python

((?<!\w)((MPH|CENT|TTXT|TTCW|TTEA|TSMA)-\d+)(?!\w))
{code}

When search query contains UTF8 non-Latin characters, URLs generated for column sorting does not contain required ampersand and become invalid.

Example repository URL (non-existing):

{{https://bitbucket.org/user/repository/issues?q=u%C5%BCytkownik}}

opens up issues page searched for {{użytkownik}} query with sort-links in columns like:

{{https://bitbucket.org/user/repository/issues?q=u%C5%BCytkowniksort=-priority}}

Notice lack of ampersand between {{?q=u%C5%BCytkownik}} and {{sort=-priority}}.

When you make a new repo and it asks you if you want to start a new project or have an existing one to push, if you select "I have an existing project to push up", the indentation on the Git cmd prompt code is wrong.

Example:

{code}
#!python

cd /path/to/my/repo  
                  git remote add origin gitthing.git
                  git push -u origin --all # pushes up the repo and its refs for the first time
                  git push -u origin --tags # pushes up any tags

{code}

It seems that if you add a commit comment with quotes in it ( " ) it&#x27;s not escaped in the JSON the API sends and therefore breaks the whole JSON formatting.

Part of response recieved

{code}
#!json

"message": "Added text for X-Axis "SportFotboll" 728x90
{code}
